com.google.iot.cbor

Interface CborNumber

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CborFloat, CborInteger

    public interface CborNumber
    Interface for CBOR data items representing numbers.

    This interface can be used to identify (and provide a uniform set of accessors for) the two data item types that represent numbers: CborInteger and CborFloat. This helps make it easier to implement the behavior described in Section 3.6 of RFC7049.

    Additionally, the byteValueExact(), shortValueExact(), and intValueExact() methods automatically perform range checks and will throw an ArithmeticException if the underlying value will not fit into the respective primitive type.

    See Also:
    CborFloat, CborInteger
